name: Adrienne Brammer
tweet: Holidays do not give you permission to get blackout drunk in the city and ride the train back home like it’s your sober buddy’s car. You do not get to hit ANYONE like it’s your due, the end of a day well spent. @NJTRANSIT

name: Adrienne Brammer
tweet: The conductor squeezed past them to open up the stairs for my stop. I hopped off and told the Latino conductor what happened. I wasn’t sure if he was still on the train, or how close those “friends” were to him. Freaking hate these drinking holidays.

name: Adrienne Brammer
tweet: Just before I got off at my stop, I overheard the remaining bro dudes asking if they had their “fake-“? Good code bro, I’m sure no one will crack that one. They planned to hit up a bar when they got home. Perfect. That’s exactly what you need to wrap up the day.

name: Adrienne Brammer
tweet: I didn’t know what to say to her. I told her I’m so sorry. Why the hell was I apologizing? He’s not my son or my brother. He’s a drunk underage loser on a train. I told her I wished her night would be better.

name: Adrienne Brammer
tweet: But I don’t think he would have hit me. I’m white. She was black. He was white. This bro dude thought he could just hit a black woman for fun. An afternoon of day drinking fun and hitting black women on the way home. I’m still angry about it.

name: Adrienne Brammer
tweet: I didn’t know what to say to her. The moment was gone. We weren’t even sure he was still on the train, maybe he’d just gotten off at the second stop. I wished he’d have tried it with me. From the moment they got on, I wished for a confrontation because they were so irritating.

name: Adrienne Brammer
tweet: Instead, she told me several stops later she overheard them saying they were slapping people on the back of the neck as they passed. That’s why she jerked. She wanted to be wrong. His face had shown surprise when she jerked, that’s what it’d said to me.

name: Adrienne Brammer
tweet: Something happened when the white bro guy passed by. The black woman next to me jerked. I thought he hadn’t looked where he was putting his hand on the seat back as he passed and had accidentally hit the side of her face.

name: Adrienne Brammer
tweet: On the way home this evening, I thought I would miss them on the way out of NYC. Nope. My train car filled to the brim, making everyone uncomfortable. The small Indian family. The small white family. And the young black woman who sat next to me - something happened.

name: Adrienne Brammer
tweet: This morning on my way into NYC, they were loud and annoying young people - all who seemed a bit young to be coming into the city for drinking. But surely that was their purpose because they weren’t with their parents for a day of touring thr city.

name: Adrienne Brammer
tweet: I freaking hate these “drinking holidays” - SantaCon, St Patrick’s Day. They’re just excuses to day drink. They bring in belligerent people from the suburbs to the city and take up space on the train. They’re loud, obnoxious, and they don’t care about anyone else around them.
